00:45:26.522 --> 00:45:27.872
and they can see humanity,

00:45:27.872 --> 00:45:30.867
you are fostering world peace.

00:45:30.867 --> 00:45:35.059
I want to finish off with
things that you can do.

00:45:35.059 --> 00:45:36.918
I promise I would throw
out some tangible ideas.

00:45:36.918 --> 00:45:39.399
The first thing is y'all
could do exactly what I did,

00:45:39.399 --> 00:45:41.327
teach things, even teach mathematics.

00:45:41.327 --> 00:45:42.928
Different types of teachers,

00:45:42.928 --> 00:45:44.839
people respond to different types

00:45:44.839 --> 00:45:46.427
of instruction all of the time.

00:45:46.427 --> 00:45:48.031
Your take on things
might connect with people

00:45:48.031 --> 00:45:49.616
and you in innovative ways.

00:45:49.616 --> 00:45:53.451
Teach English. There's no
better way to empower people

00:45:53.451 --> 00:45:54.874
in the developing world to participate

00:45:54.874 --> 00:45:57.152
in the global economy
than learning English.

00:45:57.152 --> 00:45:59.968
That's something I think
everyone in this room could do.

00:45:59.968 --> 00:46:01.436
Set up Skype buddies, so that
you can start interacting

00:46:01.436 --> 00:46:03.153
with people across the world.

